meta.description:
Yale University epidemiologist Harvey Risch is expecting insurers to seek financial compensation from Covid-19 vaccine makers to cover “early unexpected mortality claims,” as “they have a major financial risk that they have to figure out how to manage.”

Read more here:
https://www.infowars.com/posts/expect-insurance-companies-to-sue-vaccine-manufacturers-to-cover-pay-outs-for-explosion-of-early-unexpected-mortality-claims/

title: Expect Insurance Companies to Sue Vaccine Manufacturers to Cover Pay-outs For Explosion of Early Unexpected Mortality Claims
